 Maginn Archives|website=Omaha Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-20}}</ref>\n*[[Holt McCallany]], actor<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nebraskacoast.com/tag/holt-mccallany/|title=Holt McCallany|publisher=Nebraska Coast Connection & The Hollywood Salon|access-date=2019-09-20}}</ref>\n*[[Vincent J. McCauley]], [[Congregation of Holy Cross|C.S.C.]], [[Servant of God]], first Bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Fort Portal|Fort Portal]], [[Uganda]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.holycrossusa.org/article/servant-of-god-vincent-mccauley/|title=Congregation of Holy Cross|website=holycrossusa.org|access-date=2019-09-20}}</ref>\n*[[Bill McGuire (baseball)|Bill McGuire]], Major League Baseball catcher ([[Seattle Mariners]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.baseball-almanac.com/players/player.php?p=mcguibi01|title=Bill McGuire Baseball Stats by Baseball Almanac|website=baseball-almanac.com|access-date=2019-09-20}}</ref>\n*[[Tim McGuire]], college football coach<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://omahachsarchives.org/archive/register/1971-03-03_10.pdf|title=Central News Register|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref>\n*[[Scott Munter]], [[Major League Baseball]] pitcher<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/bullpen/Scott_Munter|title=Scott Munter - BR Bullpen|website=baseball-reference.com|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref>\n* Lt. Col. [[John Nagl]], assisted Gen. [[David Petraeus]] in writing the ''US Army Marine Counterinsurgency Field Manual'', current headmaster at [[The Haverford School]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thereader.com/news/retired-warrior-lifetime-scholar-and-devout-believer-john-nagl-looks-back-o|title=Retired warrior, lifetime scholar and devout believer John Nagl looks back on Army career|last=Biga|first=Leo Adam|date=2013-09-30|website=The Reader|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref>\n*[[Conor Oberst]], musician ([[Bright Eyes (band)|Bright Eyes]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.omaha.com/go/archives-that-time-a--year-old-named-conor-oberst/article_55013640-2d23-5a39-bc5c-273205971b4d.html|title=Archives: That time a 17-year-old named Conor Oberst played at open mic night|last=Mertes|first=Micah|website=Omaha.com|language=en|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref>\n*[[Alexander Payne]], film director, [[Academy Award]]-winning screenwriter<ref name=\"Schweiss\"/>\n*[[Steve Pedersen]], musician (Cursive and [[Criteria (band)|Criteria]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.creightonprep.creighton.edu/cf_news/view.cfm?newsid=1251|title=News Post|website=creightonprep.creighton.edu|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref>\n*[[Kyle Peterson]],  [[Major League Baseball]] pitcher and [[ESPN]] analyst<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.baseball-almanac.com/players/player.php?p=peterky01|title=Kyle Peterson Baseball Stats by Baseball Almanac|website=baseball-almanac.com|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref>\n*[[Zach Potter]], [[National Football League]] tight end for the [[Houston Texans]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://247sports.com/player/zach-potter-42951/|title=Zach Potter, Nebraska Cornhuskers, Strong-Side Defensive End|website=247Sports|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref>\n*[[Daniel Quinn]], author<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nebraskaauthors.org/authors/daniel-quinn|title=Daniel Quinn {{!}} Nebraska Authors|website=nebraskaauthors.org|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref>\n*[[Andrew Rannells]],  [[Grammy Award]]-winning actor and singer<ref name=\":16\" />\n*[[Albert C. Wedemeyer]], Army general<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ww2gravestone.com/people/wedemeyer-albert-coady/|title=Wedemeyer, Albert Coady|website=WW2 Gravestone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref>\n*[[Gene Williams (American football)|Gene Williams]], [[National Football League]] offensive lineman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.omaha.com/sports/local-sports/pospisil-there-s-a-long-history-of-nebraska-high-school/article_1f750740-bfa2-5eba-8014-4f4ad2840d3b.html|title=Pospisil: There\u2019s a long history of Nebraska high school grads starring elsewhere in college|